# Tech Stack & Environment Parity

## Docker-first execution (absolute parity)

Local test runs **must default to Docker wrappers** — not bare-metal `npx playwright test` for gate validation.

| Intent | Command |
| --- | --- |
| Smoke (`@smoke`) | `npm run docker:test:smoke` |
| Regression (`@regression`) | `npm run docker:test:regression` |
| Full CI suite | `npm run docker:test:ci` |
| Lint + typecheck in container | `npm run docker:lint` |

Underlying compose service (pre-push / CI parity):

```bash
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml run --rm test:smoke
```

> If it passes in Docker, it passes in CI. Never treat a local Node/OS-only run as definitive.

## Pinned versions only

- **Node:** LTS — match `.github/workflows` `node-version`
- **Playwright:** `@playwright/test` version in `package.json` must match the `mcr.microsoft.com/playwright` Docker image tag
- Do not float `latest` in `Dockerfile` or CI without explicit team approval

## Environment & secrets

- **Hardcoded credentials are forbidden** (`admin`, passwords, tokens in source)
- All config flows through layers:

```text
.env.example  →  process.env  →  src/config/environments.ts  →  playwright.config.ts
```

- Use `test.skip()` when required env vars are missing — never fail silently
- Document new variables in `.env.example` and `CONTRIBUTING.md` §7

## CI alignment

- PR pipeline: `@smoke` via `docker compose run --rm test:smoke`
- Main pipeline: `docker compose run --rm test:ci` (`--grep-invert @flaky`)
- GitHub Actions must use the same compose services as local Husky pre-push (Gate 1.3)

